{"id":"10816","name":"Goodberry's Flavor of the Day","tagline":"This shortcut will return the Flavor of the Day at Goodberry's Frozen Custard.","icon":"ios15 c4292093695 g59679","latest":"34660","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Each month, Goodberry's releases their Flavor of the Day calendar in the form of an image on their <a href=\"https://www.goodberrys.com/flavor-of-the-day\">website</a>. I <a href=\"https://alekdarr.com/blog/goodberrys-flavor-of-the-day-calendar?utm_source=routinehub.co&amp;utm_medium=flavor-of-the-day-shortcut-description-link&amp;utm_campaign=project-backlinks\">suggested some improvements</a> to their process, but I didn't hear back from them. So, I made it myself!</p>\n<p>When Goodberry's releases their Flavor of the Day calendar, I add the flavors to a Google Calendar. The Shortcut then reads the calendar, using the public link, and returns the Flavor of the Day for a given day. Having the Shortcut installed on your device will also allow you to ask Siri for the Flavor of the Day.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"iPhone 12 Pro Max displaying Goodberry's Flavor of the Day iOS Shortcut result of asking Siri &quot;What's the Flavor of the Day&quot;\" src=\"https://alekdarr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/goodberrys-flavor-of-the-day-ios-shorcut-hey-siri-cropped.png\"></p>\n<p>Additionally, the Shortcut will ask if you'd like to subscribe to the Google Calendar so that you can see the Flavor of the Day as an all-day event on your mobile device.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>3.2 - Aug. 19, 2022, 10:19 p.m.</strong></p><p>Important update. I noticed a flaw in the new API logic that would have made it difficult to add the next month's flavor before the month begins. This update should accommodate that scenario, gracefully, going forward.</p>"}